gui.analyzer.util

Class JLabelFinder

  • java.lang.Object
    • gui.analyzer.util.JLabelFinder

  • public class JLabelFinder
extends java.lang.Object
    Sometimes, components do not contain any domain information in them. However, a JLabel can describe other components. A JLabel has a labelFor attribute, which refers to the component, which this JLabel is describing.

      • existsComponentByLabelFor

        public static boolean existsComponentByLabelFor(java.lang.String labelFor,
                                java.awt.Component component)
        If there is a JLabel with the given labelFor referring to the given component, returns true. The method is used in the replay function.
        Parameters:
        labelFor - the text of the JLabel component to be compared
        component - the component, for which the JLabel component should be found with the given labelFor text.
        Returns:
        true, if a JLabel exists for the given component and with the given labelFor text, false otherwise.
